This game mode is called Salvage. Two teams contest a canister that contains a valuable resource called Soltrium.
The team with the most players near the canister will extract Soltrium and earn points for their team. This can be seen at the top of the screen.
When a canister is depleted, a new one will spawn elsewhere. The first team to reach 500 points wins!
Ammo Bonuses drop when a player dies. Pick them up to get extra ammo for your weapons and earn 2 points for your team.
This game mode is called Breakthrough. To win, your team must control all five zones.
When a zone is captured by your team, it will be frozen for up to 20 seconds. While frozen the enemy cannot retake it, which gives your team the chance to push forward into the next zone.
Zones must be captured in order and cannot be back-capped.
This game mode is called Control Shift. There is one zone and the objective is to push that zone all the way back into enemy territory.
The zone will begin moving when one team has more players inside it than the other.
This game mode is called Escort. To win, your team must deliver 3 bombs.
Each team has a bomb that they must pick up from their side of the map and deliver to the enemy bomb site.
You can either escort your bomb carrier, or defend your bomb site from the enemy.
This game mode is called Capture the Flag. Each team has a flag that they must defend.
To win your team must steal the enemy flag and take it back to your base 3 times.
You can either infiltrate the enemy base, or defend your flag from the enemy.
This game mode is called Gun Game. Each player starts with the same weapon and progresses to the next weapon after getting 2 kills.
The stage that each player is up to is shown at the top of the screen.
To win you must advance to Stage 11 and then kill an enemy with either your digger or your knife.
When dying to fall damage or an enemy digger/knife, you will be sent back one stage.
This free-for-all game mode is called Head Hunter. To win, you must hold the most Soltrium when the timer runs out.
Each player starts with nothing and collects weapons and mods from around the map.
When a player dies, they will drop their weapons, half their Soltrium and half their mods.
Pick up Soltrium to win, but be careful as the player with the most Soltrium will be revealed to everyone.
This arena game mode is called Spire. To win, you must eliminate the enemy team 5 times.
Each player starts with nothing and must build into the sky to pick up weapons.
This arena game mode is called Static. To win, you must eliminate the enemy team 5 times.
Each player shares the same loadout, which is randomised each round.
